Day 3 – Even and Odd Number Analyzer
1. Program Description

This program analyzes a range of numbers entered by the user. It counts how many numbers are even and how many are odd, and also calculates the sum of each group.

The goal is to demonstrate the use of for loops, conditional statements (if/else), and arithmetic operations.

2. Logic Used

The program works in the following steps:

2.1 Input and Validation

The user enters a starting and ending value for the range. If the starting value is greater than the ending value, the program displays an error message and stops execution.

2.2 Loop Processing

A for loop is used to go through each number in the interval. For each number:

The program checks if it is even using number % 2 == 0
Otherwise, it is considered odd
2.3 Counting and Summing
Even numbers are counted and added to sumEven
Odd numbers are counted and added to sumOdd
3. Output

At the end, the program displays:

The interval
Total numbers
Count and sum of even numbers
Count and sum of odd numbers
Which category has more numbers
4. Conclusion

This program demonstrates how to use loops and conditions to analyze numerical data. It shows how to process a range of values and produce meaningful results based on logical checks.
